---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Thematic Analysis for Market Research Consultants | Codesift"
  description="Speed up thematic analysis on qualitative survey data. Codesift helps independent researchers categorize verbatim responses in minutes."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="article">
        <h1>Thematic Analysis for Market Research Consultants</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          As an independent market research consultant, your clients expect fast turnarounds on coded qualitative data. Codesift accelerates the thematic analysis process so you can deliver professional, coded datasets in hours instead of days — without sacrificing quality or control.
        </p>

        <h2>The Consultant Workflow Reality</h2>

        <p>
          The typical qualitative coding project starts with data export from Qualtrics, SurveyMonkey, or another survey platform. You download a spreadsheet full of open-ended responses — sometimes 500 rows, sometimes 5,000 — and the clock starts ticking. Your client needs the coded results for their stakeholder presentation, often within a week.
        </p>

        <p>
          Next comes the codebook development. You read through a sample of responses, identify recurring themes, define codes with clear criteria, and document examples. This part is essential and can't be rushed — the codebook is the foundation of the analysis. But once the codebook is ready, you face the tedious part: applying those codes to every single response, one by one.
        </p>

        <p>
          Manual coding at this stage is pure repetition. You're not generating insights; you're executing a defined categorization task over and over. For a 2,000-response dataset, this can consume 20-30 hours of your time — billable hours, but not the high-value strategic work that justifies your consulting rate. And if the client wants to refine the codebook after seeing initial results, you start over.
        </p>

        <h2>How Codesift Fits Your Process</h2>

        <p>
          Codesift doesn't replace your expertise — it handles the repetitive execution after you've done the strategic thinking. You still develop the codebook (manually, or using AI assistance). You still decide what themes matter and how to define them. But instead of spending days applying those codes manually, you let Codesift process the entire dataset in minutes.
        </p>

        <p>
          The workflow integrates directly into your existing process. Export your survey data as usual and upload it to Codesift. Develop your codebook, optionally using an AI analysis of the uploaded data, or import an existing codebook. Then let the AI apply them. You get back coded data ready to import into your analysis tool or client deliverable template.
        </p>

        <p>
          Because Codesift charges by data processed rather than per response, the economics work in your favor. A typical 2,000-response dataset costs $2-5 to code, not the $40-80 you'd pay with per-response pricing tools. That pricing structure means you can use AI coding on every project — not just the huge ones — and still maintain healthy margins.
        </p>

        <h2>Client Deliverables, Faster</h2>

        <p>
          Speed matters in consulting. The faster you can deliver coded data, the sooner your client can act on insights and the sooner you can move to the next project. Codesift compresses the coding timeline from days to hours, giving you more time to focus on analysis, interpretation, and recommendation development — the parts of the project where your expertise truly shines.
        </p>

        <p>
          And when clients inevitably ask for revisions — "Can we split the 'price' code into 'too expensive' and 'good value'?" — you can re-code the entire dataset in minutes instead of starting another multi-day manual pass. That responsiveness makes you more competitive and keeps projects on track.
        </p>

        <p>
          For solo consultants and small teams, AI-assisted coding levels the playing field. You can take on larger qualitative projects that would have been impractical to code manually and deliver them with the same turnaround time and quality as bigger firms — all while keeping your overhead low and your flexibility high.
        </p>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <h3>Try It on Your Next Project</h3>
          <p>See how much time Codesift can save on your next qualitative coding project. Start free, no credit card needed.</p>
          <a href="https://app.codesift.ai" class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="related-links">
        <h3>Related resources</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/use-cases/coding-open-ended-survey-responses">AI Coding for Open-Ended Survey Responses</a></li>
          <li><a href="/use-cases/qualitative-survey-coding-ai">Qualitative Survey Coding with AI</a></li>
          <li><a href="/compare/manual-vs-ai-coding">Manual vs AI Coding Comparison</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding-top: 120px;
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  .article {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 42px;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 32px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-top: 48px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .related-links {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 48px auto 0;
    padding-top: 32px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .related-links h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .related-links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }

  .related-links a {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .related-links a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .content-page {
      padding-top: 96px;
      padding-bottom: 60px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 36px;
    }

    .cta-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
